cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PL

The paper discusses configuration interfaces from an HCI perspective, which suggests that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on system availability and the design and implementation of new-generation configuration interfaces, which are relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses obstacles to correctly and efficiently configuring software systems, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
